.TH start-cli-server-host-binding 1  "binding " 
.SH NAME
start\-cli\-server\-host\-binding \- Commands for managing host bindings
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-cli server host binding\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Commands for managing host bindings
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
start\-cli\-server\-host\-binding\-list(1)
List bindings for a host
.TP
start\-cli\-server\-host\-binding\-set\-address\-enabled(1)
Set a gateway address enabled for a binding
.TP
start\-cli\-server\-host\-binding\-set\-gua\-wan(1)
Expose an IPv6 global\-unicast address to the WAN (or revert it to LAN\-only) for a binding
.TP
start\-cli\-server\-host\-binding\-set\-range\-address\-enabled(1)
Set a gateway address enabled for a port\-range binding
